Context:
The user wanted the VS Code 2026 Dark theme ported into the local Neovim config while keeping the existing vscode.nvim plugin path. The repo already had local highlight fixups in lua/highlights.lua, plus unrelated uncommitted edits in several files, so the safest route was to add a late-loading local spec and a dedicated palette module instead of editing the dirty theme spec in place.

Rationale:
The override module mirrors the effective VS Code theme rather than only the top-level 2026-dark.json deltas. UI colors come from the explicit workbench/editor values, token groups come from the 2026 Dark overrides, and type-family colors intentionally stay near the inherited base VS Code palette where 2026 Dark does not replace them. A separate override spec keeps the upstream plugin upgrade path simple and lets the existing ColorScheme autocmd fixups continue to apply after vscode.nvim loads.

